00:24:28,842 --> 00:24:29,884
Please forgive me.

540
00:24:29,885 --> 00:24:32,178
- He looks pretty safe to me now.

541
00:24:32,179 --> 00:24:35,015
(engine whirring)

542
00:24:36,766 --> 00:24:38,642
- Nina, please help me.

543
00:24:38,643 --> 00:24:40,436
Please let me go.

544
00:24:40,437 --> 00:24:43,440
(doorknob rattling)

545
00:24:45,442 --> 00:24:47,902
(door clattering)

546
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:48,903
- Hm.

547
00:24:50,530 --> 00:24:52,616
Kaori, I'm done with the shower.

548
00:24:54,326 --> 00:24:55,659
Where did she go?

549
00:24:55,660 --> 00:24:58,580
(insects chirping)

550
00:25:07,255 --> 00:25:09,841
(Nina gasping)

551
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:11,926
Mother?

552
00:25:13,094 --> 00:25:14,720
(piano music)

553
00:25:14,721 --> 00:25:15,971
- Huh?

554
00:25:15,972 --> 00:25:17,515
- Ah, Kaori.

555
00:25:17,516 --> 00:25:18,891
I'm sorry.

556
00:25:18,892 --> 00:25:21,018
You looked very much like my mother

557
00:25:21,019 --> 00:25:23,020
from behind just a moment ago.

558
00:25:23,021 --> 00:25:24,063
- What?

559
00:25:24,064 --> 00:25:25,147
(Kaori laughing)

560
00:25:25,148 --> 00:25:26,357
Someone mistook me for a man once,

561
00:25:26,358 --> 00:25:30,027
but this is the first time
to be taken for a mother.

562
00:25:30,028 --> 00:25:31,403
- That's not what I meant.

563
00:25:31,404 --> 00:25:32,738
- What?

564
00:25:32,739 --> 00:25:35,574
- Every time I asked about my father,

565
00:25:35,575 --> 00:25:38,536
she would turn her back to me
and look through the window

566
00:25:38,537 --> 00:25:39,537
at the moon.

567
00:25:42,749 --> 00:25:45,376
I'm sure that my mother loved my father,

568
00:25:45,377 --> 00:25:49,463
but then, something happened between them.

569
00:25:49,464 --> 00:25:52,174
She was very upset, and then he left.

570
00:25:52,175 --> 00:25:53,175
Oh, what am I saying?

571
00:25:53,176 --> 00:25:54,260
She has passed on.

572
00:25:54,261 --> 00:25:55,761
It doesn't make sense.

573
00:25:55,762 --> 00:25:58,264
I'm so sorry I saw you as my mother.

574
00:25:58,265 --> 00:26:00,307
- Well, uh...

575
00:26:00,308 --> 00:26:03,186
- Tell me, Kaori, you
love Mr. Saeba, don't you?

576
00:26:04,437 --> 00:26:07,022
- How could I love someone
as perverted as him?

577
00:26:07,023 --> 00:26:09,400
Our partnership is strictly business.

578
00:26:09,401 --> 00:26:10,859
- You're better off that way.

579
00:26:10,860 --> 00:26:12,611
He's quite ridiculous.

580
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:15,864
I've never met anyone quite so perverted.

581
00:26:15,865 --> 00:26:18,535
(Nina giggling)

582
00:26:19,578 --> 00:26:20,869
- Naked men make you laugh.

583
00:26:20,870 --> 00:26:21,705
How cute.

584
00:26:21,705 --> 00:26:22,539
- Sorry.

585
00:26:22,540 --> 00:26:24,081
I couldn't help it.

586
00:26:24,082 --> 00:26:27,501
But while I was remembering
all the silly things he did,

587
00:26:27,502 --> 00:26:28,794
I just couldn't stop myself

588
00:26:28,795 --> 00:26:30,672
from laughing at the whole thing.

589
00:26:31,673 --> 00:26:34,008
- He may seem silly and spontaneous,

590
00:26:34,009 --> 00:26:37,011
but he plans that stuff
out weeks in advance.

591
00:26:37,012 --> 00:26:38,262
- Um, Kaori?

592
00:26:38,263 --> 00:26:40,806
- Anyway, now I'm thinking
it's not such a good idea

593
00:26:40,807 --> 00:26:42,349
for you to stay over.

594
00:26:42,350 --> 00:26:43,226
- Oh, no.

595
00:26:43,227 --> 00:26:47,062
Deep down, I think he's actually
an all right kind of guy.

596
00:26:47,063 --> 00:26:49,982
- Is it all right to
make love to a window?

597
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:50,817
(Nina shrieking)

598
00:26:50,817 --> 00:26:51,651
- Mr. Saeba.

599
00:26:51,652 --> 00:26:54,570
- Haven't you learned anything yet?

600
00:26:54,571 --> 00:26:58,365
(glass shattering)
(Joe screaming)

601
00:26:58,366 --> 00:27:01,201
(explosion booming)

602
00:27:01,202 --> 00:27:06,207
- Don't you think you might
be overreacting just a little?

603
00:27:06,750 --> 00:27:09,835
- An ancient Japanese proverb
says the clever play hooky

604
00:27:09,836 --> 00:27:11,503
as the week seek nookie.

605
00:27:11,504 --> 00:27:14,256
- I'm clever enough to know this is wrong.

606
00:27:14,257 --> 00:27:16,634
I'm going back to my hotel now.

607
00:27:16,635 --> 00:27:19,638
(car horns honking)

608
00:27:23,141 --> 00:27:25,810
(phone ringing)

609
00:27:27,687 --> 00:27:28,896
- Did you find Nina?

610
00:27:28,897 --> 00:27:29,938
Hello?

611
00:27:29,939 --> 00:27:31,649
- [Nina] It's me, Grandpa.

612
00:27:31,650 --> 00:27:32,484
- Nina.

613
00:27:32,485 --> 00:27:34,276
I was so terribly concerned.

614
00:27:34,277 --> 00:27:35,903
- I'm sorry to make you worry about me,

615
00:27:35,904 --> 00:27:37,446
Grandpa, but I'm all right.

616
00:27:37,447 --> 00:27:39,365
There was just something I had to do

617
00:27:39,366 --> 00:27:40,991
as soon as we got to Japan.

618
00:27:40,992 --> 00:27:41,826
- Like what?

619
00:27:41,827 --> 00:27:44,329
You have a piano here, and that is all.

620
00:27:45,455 --> 00:27:47,706
- I am trying to locate my father.

621
00:27:47,707 --> 00:27:48,707
- Your what?

622
00:27:49,834 --> 00:27:51,001
Your father.

623
00:27:51,002 --> 00:27:52,461
Oh, Nina.

624
00:27:52,462 --> 00:27:54,630
What would make you do
something like this?

625
00:27:54,631 --> 00:27:56,215
You need to get your rest.

626
00:27:56,216 --> 00:27:59,426
You have a reception tomorrow,
and then, all the concerts.

627
00:27:59,427 --> 00:28:02,388
- Don't be concerned about me, Grandpa.

628
00:28:02,389 --> 00:28:04,973
I'm on my way to the hotel.

629
00:28:04,974 --> 00:28:05,974
Yes.

630
00:28:09,896 --> 00:28:12,523
(Klaus sighing)

631
00:28:12,524 --> 00:28:15,234
- She wants to find her father.

632
00:28:15,235 --> 00:28:16,235
Idiot.

633
00:28:17,487 --> 00:28:18,654
I should have known that

634
00:28:18,655 --> 00:28:21,031
coming to Japan would be a disaster.

635
00:28:21,032 --> 00:28:22,825
(door knocking)

636
00:28:22,826 --> 00:28:24,076
Who's there?

637
00:28:24,077 --> 00:28:25,536
- [Man] Room service.

638
00:28:25,537 --> 00:28:26,829
- Room service?

639
00:28:26,830 --> 00:28:29,040
I didn't order anything from room service.

640
00:28:31,876 --> 00:28:32,711
Huh?

641
00:28:32,712 --> 00:28:34,087
Who the hell are you?

642
00:28:37,173 --> 00:28:40,634
- I realized that I would need
to get away from my grandpa

643
00:28:40,635 --> 00:28:43,345
in order to start the
search for my father.

644
00:28:43,346 --> 00:28:45,848
I knew that if he found
out I was interested,

645
00:28:45,849 --> 00:28:48,225
he wouldn't let me leave the hotel room.

646
00:28:48,226 --> 00:28:49,226
(Kaori laughing)

647
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:51,019
- And after all that, all
you have to show for it

648
00:28:51,020 --> 00:28:52,980
is a day of being hit on by Joe.

649
00:28:52,981 --> 00:28:54,565
Sorry, Nina.

650
00:28:54,566 --> 00:28:55,400
- No.

651
00:28:55,401 --> 00:28:57,109
I should have known.

652
00:28:57,110 --> 00:28:59,445
I should have known it
was going to be impossible

653
00:28:59,446 --> 00:29:02,407
to find my father with just a
stupid little clue like that.

654
00:29:03,908 --> 00:29:06,703
I just, I couldn't stop
myself from trying.

655
00:29:07,620 --> 00:29:09,163
- It's all right.

656
00:29:09,164 --> 00:29:12,332
(insects chirping)

657
00:29:12,333 --> 00:29:15,252
- You kidnapped me so we
could go for a stroll?

658
00:29:15,253 --> 00:29:18,005
- I just want you to
meet someone over there.

659
00:29:18,006 --> 00:29:18,840
(Klaus scoffing)

660
00:29:18,840 --> 00:29:19,840
- Meet someone?

661
00:29:20,884 --> 00:29:22,968
(car whirring)

662
00:29:22,969 --> 00:29:25,805
(tires squealing)

663
00:29:26,765 --> 00:29:28,557
- Grandpa, where are you going?

664
00:29:28,558 --> 00:29:29,392
- Huh?
