672
00:29:43,323 --> 00:29:46,617
What are you gonna do now, huh?

673
00:29:46,618 --> 00:29:47,452
(Kaori giggling)

674
00:29:47,453 --> 00:29:49,244
I forgot about the gun.

675
00:29:49,245 --> 00:29:51,163
- Keep your mouth shut.

676
00:29:51,164 --> 00:29:53,958
I guess we will all attend
this meeting together.

677
00:29:54,918 --> 00:29:57,294
- I don't think so.
- Joe.

678
00:29:57,295 --> 00:29:58,338
- [Nina] Mr. Saeba.

679
00:30:00,006 --> 00:30:01,673
- [Joe] You see, Nina's dance card

680
00:30:01,674 --> 00:30:03,717
is already filled this evening.

681
00:30:03,718 --> 00:30:06,053
- Hm, except I'm the DJ.

682
00:30:06,054 --> 00:30:08,848
You don't seem to
understand the situation.

683
00:30:10,475 --> 00:30:13,060
- If you're gonna shoot
me, you'd better do it now.

684
00:30:13,061 --> 00:30:14,228
- Right.

685
00:30:14,229 --> 00:30:16,522
- Mr. Saeba, don't.

686
00:30:16,523 --> 00:30:19,275
(dramatic music)

687
00:30:22,779 --> 00:30:25,697
- [Nina Voiceover] He's so
different than he was before.

688
00:30:25,698 --> 00:30:26,866
What kind of man is he?

689
00:30:28,076 --> 00:30:30,994
- Can you shoot, or is
that gun just for fashion?

690
00:30:30,995 --> 00:30:32,080
- That does it.

691
00:30:33,081 --> 00:30:34,790
(gun firing)

692
00:30:34,791 --> 00:30:35,625
But how?

693
00:30:35,626 --> 00:30:37,793
How did you fire so quickly?

694
00:30:37,794 --> 00:30:39,586
- I drink a lot of coffee.

695
00:30:39,587 --> 00:30:42,631
Well now, it doesn't seem
like your motive was robbery.

696
00:30:42,632 --> 00:30:44,716
Why don't you start explaining?

697
00:30:44,717 --> 00:30:45,552
(gun cocking)

698
00:30:45,553 --> 00:30:47,094
Huh?

699
00:30:47,095 --> 00:30:48,262
- Joe, he's getting away.

700
00:30:48,263 --> 00:30:50,138
- Don't move, I'll get him.

701
00:30:50,139 --> 00:30:52,850
(ominous music)

702
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:55,561
- Colonel Helzen, I apologize.

703
00:30:55,562 --> 00:30:57,354
- We'll discuss it later.

704
00:30:57,355 --> 00:31:00,441
- Yes.
(dramatic music)

705
00:31:09,951 --> 00:31:14,413
(Helzen grunting)
(jeep whirring)

706
00:31:14,414 --> 00:31:17,250
(tires squealing)

707
00:31:20,169 --> 00:31:23,006
(Helzen grunting)

708
00:31:26,426 --> 00:31:28,720
- City Hunter and Falcon, yes.

709
00:31:34,601 --> 00:31:36,393
- I think they're gone.

710
00:31:36,394 --> 00:31:38,103
- Well, that was pretty close,

711
00:31:38,104 --> 00:31:39,730
but I don't hear you saying thank you.

712
00:31:39,731 --> 00:31:42,149
- Ah, that's 'cause I didn't need you.

713
00:31:42,150 --> 00:31:44,735
And besides, why do you
think you had to follow me?

714
00:31:44,736 --> 00:31:46,194
- Hm, 'cause in this neighborhood,

715
00:31:46,195 --> 00:31:48,447
hormones like yours have to be on a leash.

716
00:31:48,448 --> 00:31:49,282
- What was that?

717
00:31:49,283 --> 00:31:51,283
Why you, hey, ah.

718
00:31:51,284 --> 00:31:54,161
- And just what the hell
were you doing here?

719
00:31:54,162 --> 00:31:56,330
(Joe shrieking)

720
00:31:56,331 --> 00:31:58,206
- My superior detective skills

721
00:31:58,207 --> 00:32:00,208
told me that this kind
of incident would happen.

722
00:32:00,209 --> 00:32:03,211
So I hid in the back of your
car so I could look after Nina.

723
00:32:03,212 --> 00:32:04,963
- Nina.
- Hm?

724
00:32:04,964 --> 00:32:06,673
- We're going back to the hotel.

725
00:32:06,674 --> 00:32:09,217
- Grandfather.
- Hey, Nina, wait up.

726
00:32:09,218 --> 00:32:10,178
Wait up.

727
00:32:10,179 --> 00:32:12,471
You're obviously in some kind of danger.

728
00:32:12,472 --> 00:32:14,348
I can be your bodyguard.

729
00:32:14,349 --> 00:32:15,183
You know?

730
00:32:15,184 --> 00:32:17,726
(tense music)
- Hm.

731
00:32:17,727 --> 00:32:20,520
(car horns honking)

732
00:32:20,521 --> 00:32:22,105
- That man is a professional.

733
00:32:22,106 --> 00:32:23,815
Do you know why he'd be after you?

734
00:32:23,816 --> 00:32:24,651
- No, I don't.

735
00:32:24,652 --> 00:32:25,943
Now leave us alone.

736
00:32:25,944 --> 00:32:28,028
- Grandpa.
- Sir, I don't think we're

737
00:32:28,029 --> 00:32:31,073
going anywhere until we've
heard a proper explanation.

738
00:32:31,074 --> 00:32:32,741
- Ha, do what you like.

739
00:32:32,742 --> 00:32:34,868
I'm going to bed now.

740
00:32:34,869 --> 00:32:36,954
- But our guests.

741
00:32:36,955 --> 00:32:38,914
- You should retire to bed as well.

742
00:32:38,915 --> 00:32:40,750
You have a reception tomorrow.

743
00:32:42,627 --> 00:32:43,961
- I'm sorry, everybody.

744
00:32:43,962 --> 00:32:45,921
My grandfather can be stubborn.

745
00:32:45,922 --> 00:32:48,215
- Ah, you don't need to apologize.

746
00:32:48,216 --> 00:32:50,217
So, Falcon, check this out.

747
00:32:50,218 --> 00:32:51,052
- Hm?

748
00:32:51,053 --> 00:32:52,636
- I don't really wanna
waste my whole evening

749
00:32:52,637 --> 00:32:54,930
sitting around here, and
I know you don't, right?

750
00:32:54,931 --> 00:32:57,683
So, I've got these two matches here.

751
00:32:57,684 --> 00:33:00,519
The guy who pulls the red
one has to stay here tonight.

752
00:33:00,520 --> 00:33:01,895
Go ahead.

753
00:33:01,896 --> 00:33:02,896
Pick one.

754
00:33:05,566 --> 00:33:07,442
Lucky you, you get to leave.

755
00:33:07,443 --> 00:33:09,361
I guess I have to stay.

756
00:33:09,362 --> 00:33:11,446
- Now I'm supposed to
pull one for you, right?

757
00:33:11,447 --> 00:33:12,281
- You don't need to.

758
00:33:12,281 --> 00:33:13,116
The game's over.

759
00:33:13,117 --> 00:33:15,242
No, no, no, don't, look.

760
00:33:15,243 --> 00:33:16,493
- You won too.

761
00:33:16,494 --> 00:33:18,078
I'm very happy for you.

762
00:33:18,079 --> 00:33:19,413
- Huh, I did?

763
00:33:19,414 --> 00:33:21,498
Get this, they broke off in my hand.

764
00:33:21,499 --> 00:33:24,751
What do you say we try that one more time?

765
00:33:24,752 --> 00:33:26,044
- Have a nice evening.

766
00:33:26,045 --> 00:33:27,671
Falcon and I will keep watch tonight.

767
00:33:27,672 --> 00:33:29,340
Am I making myself clear?

768
00:33:31,009 --> 00:33:31,843
- Yes, ma'am.

769
00:33:31,844 --> 00:33:33,385
I guess there's nothing I can do

770
00:33:33,386 --> 00:33:35,303
since you saw through my trick.

771
00:33:35,304 --> 00:33:37,472
I'm going home.

772
00:33:37,473 --> 00:33:40,434
- Hm, you have got to be kidding me.

773
00:33:40,435 --> 00:33:43,020
(wolf howling)

774
00:33:43,021 --> 00:33:46,857
- Ah, so Helzen intended
to meet with Shutenberg.

775
00:33:46,858 --> 00:33:49,985
When he sees Klaus again,
that will be the time.

776
00:33:49,986 --> 00:33:51,528
I'm sure of it.

777
00:33:51,529 --> 00:33:52,696
Then, you go.

778
00:33:52,697 --> 00:33:53,531
- Mm.

779
00:33:53,532 --> 00:33:55,157
I will take care of them.

780
00:33:55,158 --> 00:33:57,075
Just leave it to me.

781
00:33:57,076 --> 00:33:59,077
(car whirring)

782
00:33:59,078 --> 00:34:01,914
(tires squealing)

783
00:34:07,253 --> 00:34:09,880
