1074
00:46:49,139 --> 00:46:52,058
- I won't tell you until
you've arrested Helzen.

1075
00:46:52,059 --> 00:46:55,645
- He has diplomatic privilege,
and we have no real evidence.

1076
00:46:55,646 --> 00:46:56,938
I'm sorry.

1077
00:46:56,939 --> 00:46:58,564
- Damn.

1078
00:46:58,565 --> 00:46:59,982
You're a professional, aren't you?

1079
00:46:59,983 --> 00:47:01,943
Can't you just kill the man?

1080
00:47:01,944 --> 00:47:05,196
I'll pay you anything
you want if you kill him.

1081
00:47:05,197 --> 00:47:07,532
- Why is it you hate Helzen so much?

1082
00:47:07,533 --> 00:47:09,700
- Will you kill him or not?

1083
00:47:09,701 --> 00:47:11,661
- The reason you want to kill Helzen

1084
00:47:11,662 --> 00:47:13,412
is because of Nina, isn't it?

1085
00:47:13,413 --> 00:47:15,039
- Nina's not involved.

1086
00:47:15,040 --> 00:47:16,457
- She's not involved?

1087
00:47:16,458 --> 00:47:17,959
That's very interesting,

1088
00:47:17,960 --> 00:47:20,419
because I thought Helzen
was Nina's father.

1089
00:47:20,420 --> 00:47:21,587
(both gasping)

1090
00:47:21,588 --> 00:47:22,422
(Nina gasping)

1091
00:47:22,423 --> 00:47:24,632
- You have to be insane to say that.

1092
00:47:24,633 --> 00:47:27,510
- His name, Johann Frederiech von Helzen.

1093
00:47:27,511 --> 00:47:32,098
His first name is Johann,
spelled J-O-H-A-N-N.

1094
00:47:32,099 --> 00:47:34,767
J is the same first
initial that's engraved

1095
00:47:34,768 --> 00:47:36,811
in the back of Nina's pendant.

1096
00:47:36,812 --> 00:47:37,854
- Coincidence.

1097
00:47:37,855 --> 00:47:39,146
- [Reika] Not at all.

1098
00:47:39,147 --> 00:47:40,231
(Klaus gasping)

1099
00:47:40,232 --> 00:47:41,567
- [Kaori] Reika.

1100
00:47:43,151 --> 00:47:44,610
- What are you doing here?

1101
00:47:44,611 --> 00:47:46,445
- Joe came over late the other night

1102
00:47:46,446 --> 00:47:47,655
and asked me to help him out

1103
00:47:47,656 --> 00:47:49,782
with an investigation of Mr. Helzen.

1104
00:47:49,783 --> 00:47:51,409
- Wait, the real reason Joe

1105
00:47:51,410 --> 00:47:52,994
went to you the other night was for-

1106
00:47:52,995 --> 00:47:54,121
- Well, now you know.

1107
00:47:55,205 --> 00:47:57,874
His real name is Johann
Frederiech von Helzen.

1108
00:47:57,875 --> 00:48:00,167
It seems that he had
stayed in West Galiera

1109
00:48:00,168 --> 00:48:02,962
something close to 20 years
ago as a special member

1110
00:48:02,963 --> 00:48:05,172
of the East Galiera embassy.

1111
00:48:05,173 --> 00:48:08,259
He was also a big fan
of Sophia Shutenberg,

1112
00:48:08,260 --> 00:48:09,677
who was Nina's mother.

1113
00:48:09,678 --> 00:48:11,387
He constantly went to her concerts

1114
00:48:11,388 --> 00:48:14,849
and was seen in her company
on several occasions.

1115
00:48:14,850 --> 00:48:17,144
- Now do you feel like
telling us the story?

1116
00:48:19,229 --> 00:48:20,439
- If I must.

1117
00:48:22,816 --> 00:48:26,110
20 years ago, at the
celebration for the detente

1118
00:48:26,111 --> 00:48:28,571
between East and West Galiera.

1119
00:48:28,572 --> 00:48:32,950
We were introduced to
two brand-new diplomats.

1120
00:48:32,951 --> 00:48:35,953
Both of them had great
skill at playing piano

1121
00:48:35,954 --> 00:48:38,248
and were enamored of my daughter, Sophia.

1122
00:48:39,458 --> 00:48:42,752
After awhile, my daughter
began a relationship

1123
00:48:42,753 --> 00:48:44,170
with one of them.

1124
00:48:44,171 --> 00:48:45,254
That was Helzen.

1125
00:48:45,255 --> 00:48:47,715
Sophia was betrayed by him.

1126
00:48:47,716 --> 00:48:49,383
He had been using my daughter

1127
00:48:49,384 --> 00:48:51,928
to cover his spying activities.

1128
00:48:51,929 --> 00:48:53,930
He left my daughter behind.

1129
00:48:53,931 --> 00:48:57,683
And then later, Sophia
gave birth to his child.

1130
00:48:57,684 --> 00:48:58,518
Poor girl.

1131
00:48:58,519 --> 00:49:00,686
She has never been told.

1132
00:49:00,687 --> 00:49:02,605
(Nina whimpering)

1133
00:49:02,606 --> 00:49:03,940
- [Nina Voiceover] That man.

1134
00:49:03,941 --> 00:49:08,611
That gentleman by the
elevator was my father.

1135
00:49:08,612 --> 00:49:11,448
(Nina whimpering)

1136
00:49:13,200 --> 00:49:14,659
- I know.

1137
00:49:14,660 --> 00:49:17,244
The charity concert
will go on as scheduled.

1138
00:49:17,245 --> 00:49:19,330
We will not disappoint you again.

1139
00:49:19,331 --> 00:49:20,915
Goodnight.

1140
00:49:20,916 --> 00:49:23,418
(dog barking)

1141
00:49:30,759 --> 00:49:31,884
- Hello, sun.

1142
00:49:31,885 --> 00:49:34,303
Time to nookie.

1143
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:39,309
Size one, two, three, four,
five, six, seven, eight.

1144
00:49:39,393 --> 00:49:43,187
The more I get of nookie
now, the less I have to...

1145
00:49:43,188 --> 00:49:44,314
Seven, eight.

1146
00:49:46,274 --> 00:49:47,274
Oh.

1147
00:49:48,527 --> 00:49:49,527
Nookie.

1148
00:49:51,863 --> 00:49:52,823
Good morning.

1149
00:49:52,824 --> 00:49:54,323
- [Nina] Good morning?

1150
00:49:54,324 --> 00:49:56,283
It's already afternoon now.

1151
00:49:56,284 --> 00:49:59,036
- You didn't get very much
sleep last night, did you, Nina?

1152
00:49:59,037 --> 00:50:01,288
Your eyes look a little red to me.

1153
00:50:01,289 --> 00:50:02,124
(Nina gasping)

1154
00:50:02,124 --> 00:50:03,124
- Oh, you can tell?

1155
00:50:04,710 --> 00:50:05,669
Please tell me.

1156
00:50:05,670 --> 00:50:09,672
Why do you think my father
had to leave my mother?

1157
00:50:09,673 --> 00:50:11,257
- Hm?
- Oh.

1158
00:50:11,258 --> 00:50:13,927
- Did you hear what we were
talking about last night?

1159
00:50:15,095 --> 00:50:17,638
Well, even if we wanted to hide the story,

1160
00:50:17,639 --> 00:50:19,974
you would've found out
sooner or later, I guess.

1161
00:50:19,975 --> 00:50:23,019
- Mr. Saeba, do you really
believe that my father

1162
00:50:23,020 --> 00:50:24,854
meant to use my mother?

1163
00:50:24,855 --> 00:50:26,856
He seemed like such a gentleman.

1164
00:50:26,857 --> 00:50:28,065
I simply can't believe

1165
00:50:28,066 --> 00:50:29,608
he would have done something like that.

1166
00:50:29,609 --> 00:50:30,860
- Wait a second.

1167
00:50:30,861 --> 00:50:31,986
You met him?

1168
00:50:31,987 --> 00:50:32,821
- Yes.

1169
00:50:32,822 --> 00:50:34,739
Back at the hotel.

1170
00:50:34,740 --> 00:50:37,575
And he had these eyes that were so sad

1171
00:50:37,576 --> 00:50:39,285
and were also so gentle.

1172
00:50:39,286 --> 00:50:42,788
He seemed so terribly sad and alone to me.

1173
00:50:42,789 --> 00:50:45,750
I don't understand how
he could have left her.

1174
00:50:45,751 --> 00:50:46,585
- Hm.

1175
00:50:46,586 --> 00:50:48,252
Don't cast judgment yet.

1176
00:50:48,253 --> 00:50:51,172
There are situations where a
man has to end a relationship

1177
00:50:51,173 --> 00:50:53,340
with a woman because he loves her.

1178
00:50:53,341 --> 00:50:55,134
- I don't want to be like that.

1179
00:50:55,135 --> 00:50:57,470
If I love you, I should be near you.

1180
00:50:57,471 --> 00:50:58,430
Oh.

1181
00:50:58,431 --> 00:51:00,723
(Kaori gasping)

1182
00:51:00,724 --> 00:51:02,808
(Joe laughing)

1183
00:51:02,809 --> 00:51:04,393
- I am suddenly really hungry.

1184
00:51:04,394 --> 00:51:06,645
Gee, I wonder what's for lunch today.

1185
00:51:06,646 --> 00:51:07,646
(Kaori shrieking)

1186
00:51:07,647 --> 00:51:09,356
- Time to go, time to go.

1187
00:51:09,357 --> 00:51:12,110
(Nina chuckling)

1188
00:51:13,278 --> 00:51:14,112
- Ha.

1189
00:51:14,113 --> 00:51:15,696
City Hunter, eh?

1190
00:51:15,697 --> 00:51:16,822
Pathetic.

1191
00:51:16,823 --> 00:51:19,241
You ran away from just one man.

1192
00:51:19,242 --> 00:51:20,659
- Please let me explain.

1193
00:51:20,660 --> 00:51:22,578
- We don't have any other choice now.

1194
00:51:22,579 --> 00:51:24,580
We have to call them in.

1195
00:51:24,581 --> 00:51:26,332
- That's not a good idea.

1196
00:51:26,333 --> 00:51:27,250
- Shut up.

1197
00:51:27,251 --> 00:51:28,584
You failed what you're supposed to do,

1198
00:51:28,585 --> 00:51:30,127
and now you're out of ideas.

1199
00:51:30,128 --> 00:51:33,047
Stop arguing and call
in the team right now.

1200
00:51:33,048 --> 00:51:34,424
- Yes, Ambassador.

1201
00:51:37,219 --> 00:51:40,889
- A conspiracy of imbeciles
is plotting against me.

1202
00:51:42,057 --> 00:51:44,893
(thunder roaring)

1203
00:51:48,522 --> 00:51:52,149
(lightning crackling)

1204
00:51:52,150 --> 00:51:54,652
(thunder rumbling)

1205
00:51:54,653 --> 00:51:57,571
(rain pattering)

1206
00:51:57,572 --> 00:52:00,408
(Kaori shrieking)

1207
00:52:03,995 --> 00:52:05,830
- Why did it have to rain all of a sudden?

1208
00:52:05,831 --> 00:52:07,748
It always makes my hair frizz out.

1209
00:52:07,749 --> 00:52:10,919
(lightning crackling)

1210
00:52:11,837 --> 00:52:15,506
(helicopter whirring)

1211
00:52:15,507 --> 00:52:18,759
(lightning crackling)

1212
00:52:18,760 --> 00:52:22,680
(lightning crackling)

1213
00:52:22,681 --> 00:52:25,641
(lightning crackling)

1214
00:52:25,642 --> 00:52:29,061
(helicopter whirring)

1215
00:52:29,062 --> 00:52:31,564
(lightning crackling)
(thunder rumbling)

1216
00:52:31,565 --> 00:52:34,692
(car horn honking)

1217
00:52:34,693 --> 00:52:37,112
(gun firing)

1218
00:52:41,074 --> 00:52:42,616
- That's incredible.

1219
00:52:42,617 --> 00:52:45,703
- Anybody can shoot like that
if they practice long enough.

1220
00:52:45,704 --> 00:52:47,454
Do you wanna try?

1221
00:52:47,455 --> 00:52:48,455
- Mm-mm.

1222
00:52:49,791 --> 00:52:52,168
You know, it's like
you're a different person

1223
00:52:52,169 --> 00:52:53,961
when you hold a gun, Mr. Saeba.

1224
00:52:53,962 --> 00:52:57,047
Usually, you are unreliable and perverted.

1225
00:52:57,048 --> 00:52:59,216
- Would you stop calling me perverted?

1226
00:52:59,217 --> 00:53:01,552
I'm what you call nookie-dependent.

1227
00:53:01,553 --> 00:53:02,845
- I don't understand.

1228
00:53:02,846 --> 00:53:04,305
What's the difference?

1229
00:53:04,306 --> 00:53:07,474
- It's complicated, like me.

1230
00:53:07,475 --> 00:53:11,187
- I wish I could always talk
so freely like we are now.

1231
00:53:11,188 --> 00:53:12,022
- Huh?

1232
00:53:12,023 --> 00:53:15,316
- I want to ask my father
why he abandoned my mother.

1233
00:53:15,317 --> 00:53:16,776
I want to see him again.

1234
00:53:17,736 --> 00:53:19,403
- So why can't you?

1235
00:53:19,404 --> 00:53:21,530
I'll make sure you have
the chance to see him again

1236
00:53:21,531 --> 00:53:23,782
before your tour is over.

1237
00:53:23,783 --> 00:53:24,618
- Huh?

1238
00:53:24,619 --> 00:53:26,285
You will, really?

1239
00:53:26,286 --> 00:53:27,078
- Really.

1240
00:53:27,079 --> 00:53:28,495
I promise.

1241
00:53:28,496 --> 00:53:30,539
Nookie time.

1242
00:53:30,540 --> 00:53:32,583
Don't be coy.

1243
00:53:32,584 --> 00:53:34,084
(Joe shrieking)
(Nina grunting)

1244
00:53:34,085 --> 00:53:35,753
- Was that coy?

1245
00:53:35,754 --> 00:53:38,631
- And just where did
you happen to get that?

1246
00:53:38,632 --> 00:53:41,050
- Um, well, from Kaori?

1247
00:53:41,051 --> 00:53:42,676
- Bad Kaori.

1248
00:53:42,677 --> 00:53:44,637
(helicopter whirring)

1249
00:53:44,638 --> 00:53:46,138
Huh?

1250
00:53:46,139 --> 00:53:47,139
- Move out.

1251
00:53:49,643 --> 00:53:51,936
(thunder rumbling)

1252
00:53:51,937 --> 00:53:54,940
(soldiers grunting)

1253
00:53:59,069 --> 00:54:00,152
- Stay here.

1254
00:54:00,153 --> 00:54:02,071
- Mr. Saeba, what's the matter?

1255
00:54:02,072 --> 00:54:04,657
- Time to greet our visitors.

1256
00:54:04,658 --> 00:54:07,368
(thrilling rock music)

1257
00:54:07,369 --> 00:54:09,955
(Joe grunting)

1258
00:54:11,581 --> 00:54:13,415
(soldiers grunting)
- Who's there?

1259
00:54:13,416 --> 00:54:16,585
(Klaus grunting)

1260
00:54:16,586 --> 00:54:18,963
(Joe panting)

1261
00:54:18,964 --> 00:54:20,714
(elevator bell ringing)

1262
00:54:20,715 --> 00:54:23,218
(guns firing)

1263
00:54:25,428 --> 00:54:26,263
(Kaori gasping)

1264
00:54:26,264 --> 00:54:27,514
- Machine guns.

1265
00:54:28,390 --> 00:54:30,892
(guns firing)

1266
00:54:31,851 --> 00:54:33,769
Bring him back here.

1267
00:54:33,770 --> 00:54:34,604
(soldier grunting)

1268
00:54:34,605 --> 00:54:36,897
(machine gun firing)
(Kaori shrieking)

1269
00:54:36,898 --> 00:54:39,401
(guns firing)

1270
00:54:41,403 --> 00:54:42,362
- Crap.

1271
00:54:42,363 --> 00:54:44,571
(window shattering)

1272
00:54:44,572 --> 00:54:46,907
(explosion booming)

1273
00:54:46,908 --> 00:54:48,951
(Joe yelling)

1274
00:54:48,952 --> 00:54:52,079
(Joe grunting)

1275
00:54:52,080 --> 00:54:55,374
(soldier panting)

1276
00:54:55,375 --> 00:54:58,044
(Kaori panting)

1277
00:55:00,088 --> 00:55:05,093
(thunder rumbling)
(soldiers panting)

1278
00:55:06,803 --> 00:55:07,637
- Hm.

1279
00:55:07,638 --> 00:55:09,346
Guess the opposition wasn't everything

1280
00:55:09,347 --> 00:55:11,099
it was cracked up to be.

1281
00:55:12,100 --> 00:55:12,934
(Kaori panting)

1282
00:55:12,935 --> 00:55:15,394
- Stop, get back here.

1283
00:55:15,395 --> 00:55:18,063
(thunder rumbling)

1284
00:55:18,064 --> 00:55:19,732
You can't take Klaus.

1285
00:55:19,733 --> 00:55:24,654
(Joe panting)
(rock music)

1286
00:55:27,407 --> 00:55:28,657
What was I thinking?

1287
00:55:28,658 --> 00:55:29,658
Help!

1288
00:55:31,161 --> 00:55:33,997
(thunder roaring)

1289
00:55:34,914 --> 00:55:35,915
- Oh, Kaori.

1290
00:55:36,791 --> 00:55:39,544
(rain pattering)

1291
00:55:41,296 --> 00:55:43,964
- Our field unit reports that Bondal

1292
00:55:43,965 --> 00:55:46,675
has assigned a special forces group.

1293
00:55:46,676 --> 00:55:47,969
- He's gone too far.

1294
00:55:49,554 --> 00:55:52,931
(engine revving)

1295
00:55:52,932 --> 00:55:55,769
(thunder roaring)

1296
00:55:59,272 --> 00:56:04,277
(water splashing)
(engine revving)

1297
00:56:06,905 --> 00:56:09,824
(bullets clicking)

1298
00:56:13,244 --> 00:56:15,412
- I'll come up with
some way to rescue them.

1299
00:56:15,413 --> 00:56:16,622
Don't worry about a thing.

1300
00:56:16,623 --> 00:56:17,623
I'll be back soon.

1301
00:56:17,624 --> 00:56:18,832
- I'm so sorry.

1302
00:56:18,833 --> 00:56:22,461
Kaori is in great danger because
of my grandfather and me.

1303
00:56:22,462 --> 00:56:25,047
- Hey, that comes with the job.

1304
00:56:25,048 --> 00:56:27,674
- Every time she's in
danger, you have saved her.

1305
00:56:27,675 --> 00:56:28,510
- She's my partner.

1306
00:56:28,511 --> 00:56:30,511
That's part of the job too.

1307
00:56:30,512 --> 00:56:32,012
- I am envious.

1308
00:56:32,013 --> 00:56:33,472
She is very lucky.

1309
00:56:33,473 --> 00:56:34,973
- Hm?

1310
00:56:34,974 --> 00:56:37,644
- Mr. Saeba, can't you
please take me with you?

1311
00:56:40,522 --> 00:56:43,774
- Nina, danger is my job, and
you can't help me with that

1312
00:56:43,775 --> 00:56:46,402
any more than I can help you
play the piano beautifully

1313
00:56:46,403 --> 00:56:48,320
at the charity concert.

1314
00:56:48,321 --> 00:56:49,321
Understand?

1315
00:56:50,865 --> 00:56:52,116
- Yes.

1316
00:56:52,117 --> 00:56:53,325
- Now, listen.

1317
00:56:53,326 --> 00:56:56,453
I'm afraid I might not be able
to keep the promise I made

1318
00:56:56,454 --> 00:56:59,748
to you about seeing your father again.

1319
00:56:59,749 --> 00:57:00,583
- All right.

1320
00:57:00,584 --> 00:57:02,042
I understand.

1321
00:57:02,043 --> 00:57:04,920
- Would it be possible for
me to borrow your pendant?

1322
00:57:04,921 --> 00:57:08,173
(Nina gasping)

1323
00:57:08,174 --> 00:57:09,174
- Of course.

1324
00:57:13,763 --> 00:57:16,765
(gear clicking)
(bell chiming)

1325
00:57:16,766 --> 00:57:18,684
- Yeah, that's what I figured.

1326
00:57:18,685 --> 00:57:20,936
- I should have guessed.
- Huh?

1327
00:57:20,937 --> 00:57:22,563
(Nina gasping)

1328
00:57:22,564 --> 00:57:26,316
- If I asked really nicely,
would you give it to me?

1329
00:57:26,317 --> 00:57:28,987
(bird chirping)

1330
00:57:32,449 --> 00:57:35,325
(engine revving)

1331
00:57:35,326 --> 00:57:37,996
(gate clacking)

1332
00:57:39,205 --> 00:57:41,958
(engine revving)

1333
00:57:45,962 --> 00:57:48,881
(brakes squealing)

1334
00:57:48,882 --> 00:57:51,925
- You still refuse to tell us, do you?

1335
00:57:51,926 --> 00:57:53,844
- [Klaus] I told you, I don't know.

1336
00:57:53,845 --> 00:57:56,930
- And I don't believe you,
so don't grow too attached

1337
00:57:56,931 --> 00:57:59,600
to this girl we found
clinging to the bottom

1338
00:57:59,601 --> 00:58:02,769
of our helicopter, because she dies.

1339
00:58:02,770 --> 00:58:03,605
- [Klaus] Stop it.

1340
00:58:03,606 --> 00:58:06,190
This girl has nothing to do with us.

1341
00:58:06,191 --> 00:58:07,191
- Where is it?

1342
00:58:08,234 --> 00:58:10,486
- It's well hidden.

1343
00:58:10,487 --> 00:58:11,862
- In the pendant.

1344
00:58:11,863 --> 00:58:14,490
The information which
Kihliman had is currently

1345
00:58:14,491 --> 00:58:17,494
inside the pendant which
Klaus' granddaughter wears.

1346
00:58:18,453 --> 00:58:19,661
- Damn you to hell.

1347
00:58:19,662 --> 00:58:21,914
That man, Helzen, is a brazen liar.

1348
00:58:21,915 --> 00:58:23,832
- Then tell us where it is, Klaus.

1349
00:58:23,833 --> 00:58:24,917
- No.

1350
00:58:24,918 --> 00:58:26,752
How much longer will you make us suffer

1351
00:58:26,753 --> 00:58:28,754
until you're satisfied?

1352
00:58:28,755 --> 00:58:32,841
- Ambassador Bondal, why did
you break your promise with me?

1353
00:58:32,842 --> 00:58:36,386
- You have been too slow on
making progress on the mission.

1354
00:58:36,387 --> 00:58:39,598
- And our unit is bored of just training.

1355
00:58:39,599 --> 00:58:42,434
We were looking forward to
enjoying an actual battle,

1356
00:58:42,435 --> 00:58:44,937
but it was a little disappointing.

1357
00:58:44,938 --> 00:58:47,356
- I wouldn't advise you
to underestimate Saeba,

1358
00:58:47,357 --> 00:58:48,732
Lieutenant Laipnitz.

1359
00:58:48,733 --> 00:58:51,528
He may cause you to regret
your overconfidence.

1360
00:58:53,947 --> 00:58:55,864
- Ha, what a wimp.

1361
00:58:55,865 --> 00:58:58,535
The illustrious Red Grim Reaper.

1362
00:59:00,078 --> 00:59:02,579
- [Joe] This is where
the helicopter went to.

1363
00:59:02,580 --> 00:59:03,914
- Wow, you're pretty good.

1364
00:59:03,915 --> 00:59:07,292
It's a gorgeous athletics
club called Etrengere.

1365
00:59:07,293 --> 00:59:09,253
Word has it that it started as a hobby

1366
00:59:09,254 --> 00:59:11,421
of a billionaire from Europe.

1367
00:59:11,422 --> 00:59:13,465
We have reason to
believe that East Galiera

1368
00:59:13,466 --> 00:59:15,008
is using this place as a cover

1369
00:59:15,009 --> 00:59:18,136
for a training facility
for their elite soldiers.

1370
00:59:18,137 --> 00:59:19,805
- Then why hasn't the police department

1371
00:59:19,806 --> 00:59:22,683
already done something about this place?

1372
00:59:22,684 --> 00:59:23,892
- We couldn't move in.

1373
00:59:23,893 --> 00:59:25,727
There was no evidence to be had.

1374
00:59:25,728 --> 00:59:28,605
- Being a cop can be
such a hassle sometimes.

1375
00:59:28,606 --> 00:59:30,233
Oh yeah, I'm not a cop.

1376
00:59:31,484 --> 00:59:35,780
So, if nobody minds,
I'll just hold onto this.

1377
00:59:39,325 --> 00:59:40,285
- Please.

1378
00:59:40,286 --> 00:59:41,952
Mr. Saeba, wait a second.

1379
00:59:41,953 --> 00:59:43,579
Please tell me one thing.

1380
00:59:43,580 --> 00:59:45,581
Why haven't you accepted
that there might be

1381
00:59:45,582 --> 00:59:48,292
a special relationship
between you and Kaori?

1382
00:59:48,293 --> 00:59:49,876
- Well.

1383
00:59:49,877 --> 00:59:50,877
- Hm?

1384
00:59:52,046 --> 00:59:54,923
- Kaori wants to love
someone for a whole lifetime.

1385
00:59:54,924 --> 00:59:56,968
My lifestyle makes that impossible.

1386
00:59:57,927 --> 01:00:01,221
- Did my father share that same feeling?

1387
01:00:01,222 --> 01:00:04,725
- He strikes me as someone
who, deep down, is very gentle.

1388
01:00:04,726 --> 01:00:06,978
I don't think he could
hurt someone he loved.

1389
01:00:15,278 --> 01:00:17,738
- Gonna keep all the fun to yourself?

1390
01:00:17,739 --> 01:00:20,866
- Having trouble digging
up adventure on your own?

1391
01:00:20,867 --> 01:00:21,701
- Ha.

1392
01:00:21,702 --> 01:00:23,285
You always were greedy.

1393
01:00:23,286 --> 01:00:26,872
- Oh, there might be some
tidbits left over for you,

1394
01:00:26,873 --> 01:00:28,999
if you're also willing to drive.

1395
01:00:29,000 --> 01:00:30,334
- I don't need much.

1396
01:00:30,335 --> 01:00:32,753
Just wanna try out a few new gadgets.

1397
01:00:32,754 --> 01:00:35,506
(engine revving)

1398
01:00:38,384 --> 01:00:41,012
(ominous music)

1399
01:00:49,687 --> 01:00:52,564
(Klaus whimpering)
(Kaori sighing)

1400
01:00:52,565 --> 01:00:54,024
(metal clacking)

1401
01:00:54,025 --> 01:00:55,025
- Huh?

1402
01:00:56,819 --> 01:00:58,779
Not satisfied yet, Helzen?

1403
01:00:58,780 --> 01:01:00,864
Haven't we suffered enough?

1404
01:01:00,865 --> 01:01:02,574
- You would have confessed sooner or later

1405
01:01:02,575 --> 01:01:04,993
since Laipnitz was the
one dealing with you.

1406
01:01:04,994 --> 01:01:06,370
I was trying to spare you.

1407
01:01:06,371 --> 01:01:08,330
- But now they're after Nina.

1408
01:01:08,331 --> 01:01:10,582
- They won't make a move until tomorrow.

1409
01:01:10,583 --> 01:01:12,542
So we still have a little time

1410
01:01:12,543 --> 01:01:14,544
for Mr. Saeba to hunt us down.

1411
01:01:14,545 --> 01:01:15,838
- But what do you mean?

1412
01:01:21,302 --> 01:01:24,054
Stop, help, dirty old man!

1413
01:01:24,055 --> 01:01:26,807
- This is a transmitter, isn't it?

1414
01:01:26,808 --> 01:01:27,974
- It could be.

1415
01:01:27,975 --> 01:01:28,851
You noticed that?

1416
01:01:28,852 --> 01:01:30,519
Good eyes.

1417
01:01:30,520 --> 01:01:31,354
Wait.

1418
01:01:31,355 --> 01:01:33,522
There's something important
we need for you to tell us.

1419
01:01:33,523 --> 01:01:35,357
Why did you separate from Sophia?

1420
01:01:35,358 --> 01:01:36,858
Nina has been suffering from the thought

1421
01:01:36,859 --> 01:01:38,902
that her father didn't love her mother.

1422
01:01:38,903 --> 01:01:42,322
- Did Nina finally find out
about my relation to her?

1423
01:01:42,323 --> 01:01:44,116
- Answer the question.

1424
01:01:44,117 --> 01:01:48,662
- I think that answer needs to
wait until Mr. Saeba is here.

1425
01:01:48,663 --> 01:01:51,665
What I must say, I could explain it better

1426
01:01:51,666 --> 01:01:53,583
if he were present at the time.

1427
01:01:53,584 --> 01:01:54,752
- [Kaori] Huh?

1428
01:01:57,755 --> 01:01:59,841
- So, Nina knows the truth.

1429
01:02:00,675 --> 01:02:03,468
- I guess she was eavesdropping
on them last night.

1430
01:02:03,469 --> 01:02:04,929
- This is my fault.

1431
01:02:07,348 --> 01:02:10,392
If I hadn't been so foolish
and taken that damn thing

1432
01:02:10,393 --> 01:02:13,478
from Kihliman, this
wouldn't have happened.

1433
01:02:13,479 --> 01:02:14,313
- Don't blame yourself.

1434
01:02:14,313 --> 01:02:15,148
It'll work out.

1435
01:02:15,149 --> 01:02:16,898
And besides, Joe will come through for us.

1436
01:02:16,899 --> 01:02:17,859
I know it.

1437
01:02:17,860 --> 01:02:18,860
- Why?
- Huh?

1438
01:02:20,486 --> 01:02:22,905
- That man, Saeba, your partner?

1439
01:02:23,865 --> 01:02:26,825
Why do you find men like him so appealing?

1440
01:02:26,826 --> 01:02:28,535
They are always chasing someone

1441
01:02:28,536 --> 01:02:31,164
or in the crosshairs
of someone even worse.

1442
01:02:32,123 --> 01:02:33,123
- Well, I...

1443
01:02:34,208 --> 01:02:36,877
- Why do women insist
on sharing their lives

1444
01:02:36,878 --> 01:02:38,712
with such dangerous men?

1445
01:02:38,713 --> 01:02:41,173
It makes no sense.

1446
01:02:41,174 --> 01:02:42,716
- Oh.

1447
01:02:42,717 --> 01:02:45,385
(car horns honking)

1448
01:02:45,386 --> 01:02:48,556
(audience applauding)

1449
01:03:05,990 --> 01:03:07,491
(Sandra sighing)

1450
01:03:07,492 --> 01:03:10,202
- [Nina Voiceover] Mr.
Saeba, in this entire world,

1451
01:03:10,203 --> 01:03:14,372
I only have faith in my
father, my mother, and you.

1452
01:03:14,373 --> 01:03:16,917
It's because of this faith
that you have given me

1453
01:03:16,918 --> 01:03:18,544
I can perform tonight.

1454
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:22,923
(piano music)

1455
01:03:22,924 --> 01:03:24,591
(rocket firing)

1456
01:03:24,592 --> 01:03:26,426
(explosion booming)

1457
01:03:26,427 --> 01:03:27,594
(men grunting)

1458
01:03:27,595 --> 01:03:30,097
(guns firing)

1459
01:03:33,226 --> 01:03:35,644
- [Laipnitz] What's going on out there?

1460
01:03:35,645 --> 01:03:38,772
- Lieutenant, there are two
intruders on the grounds.

1461
01:03:38,773 --> 01:03:39,773
- Two intruders?

1462
01:03:40,525 --> 01:03:43,235
They have done well so far for amateurs,

1463
01:03:43,236 --> 01:03:45,655
but they're due for a rude awakening.

1464
01:03:47,615 --> 01:03:49,367
Time for them to die.

1465
01:03:50,868 --> 01:03:53,286
(rocket firing)

1466
01:03:53,287 --> 01:03:55,789
(explosion booming)

1467
01:03:55,790 --> 01:03:58,918
(machine guns firing)

1468
01:04:00,253 --> 01:04:02,755
(guns firing)

1469
01:04:04,257 --> 01:04:06,759
(guns firing)

1470
01:04:07,760 --> 01:04:09,886
(Joe panting)

1471
01:04:09,887 --> 01:04:12,390
(guns firing)

1472
01:04:14,392 --> 01:04:16,476
(Falcon grunting)

1473
01:04:16,477 --> 01:04:18,980
(guns firing)

1474
01:04:20,022 --> 01:04:22,190
