1490
01:05:33,930 --> 01:05:37,682
(glass shattering)
(guns firing)

1491
01:05:37,683 --> 01:05:40,101
(soldier grunting)

1492
01:05:40,102 --> 01:05:41,937
(gun firing)

1493
01:05:41,938 --> 01:05:43,772
(chandelier shattering)
(soldiers shrieking)

1494
01:05:43,773 --> 01:05:46,275
(guns firing)

1495
01:05:51,197 --> 01:05:55,992
(glass shattering)
(machine guns firing)

1496
01:05:55,993 --> 01:06:00,664
(machine gun firing)
(soldiers shrieking)

1497
01:06:00,665 --> 01:06:05,670
(machine gun firing)
(soldiers screaming)

1498
01:06:06,754 --> 01:06:07,588
(Falcon chuckling)

1499
01:06:07,589 --> 01:06:09,297
- Ah, you big showoff.

1500
01:06:09,298 --> 01:06:10,800
- I'd say we're even now.

1501
01:06:11,676 --> 01:06:14,636
(guns firing)

1502
01:06:14,637 --> 01:06:16,388
- [Laipnitz] Haven't
you finished them yet?

1503
01:06:16,389 --> 01:06:17,348
- No, sir.

1504
01:06:17,349 --> 01:06:21,017
They have much more firepower
than we anticipated.

1505
01:06:21,018 --> 01:06:22,936
- You are all cowards.

1506
01:06:22,937 --> 01:06:25,522
- Lieutenant Laipnitz.
(Laipnitz growling)

1507
01:06:25,523 --> 01:06:27,565
Are you sure we're still all right?

1508
01:06:27,566 --> 01:06:28,733
We appear to be in trouble.

1509
01:06:28,734 --> 01:06:30,527
- Will you quit complaining?

1510
01:06:30,528 --> 01:06:32,445
There are only two of them,

1511
01:06:32,446 --> 01:06:35,281
and they won't be alive much longer.

1512
01:06:35,282 --> 01:06:36,117
- I see.

1513
01:06:36,118 --> 01:06:37,283
I trust you.

1514
01:06:37,284 --> 01:06:39,787
(guns firing)

1515
01:06:40,871 --> 01:06:43,331
- It sure is noisy outside.

1516
01:06:43,332 --> 01:06:46,042
That must be Joe coming to rescue us.

1517
01:06:46,043 --> 01:06:48,461
I told you we'd be okay.

1518
01:06:48,462 --> 01:06:51,840
- How can you make yourself
cheerful right now?

1519
01:06:51,841 --> 01:06:52,800
- What?

1520
01:06:52,801 --> 01:06:55,261
- Aren't you the least
bit upset or frightened?

1521
01:06:57,263 --> 01:06:58,888
- Yeah.

1522
01:06:58,889 --> 01:07:01,433
I am scared to death right now.

1523
01:07:01,434 --> 01:07:04,185
But that doesn't mean
I have to be unhappy.

1524
01:07:04,186 --> 01:07:05,270
I believe in him.

1525
01:07:05,271 --> 01:07:08,481
In my heart, I always knew
that Joe would save me.

1526
01:07:08,482 --> 01:07:10,985
(guns firing)

1527
01:07:12,528 --> 01:07:14,863
- Don't you care for Sophia at all?

1528
01:07:14,864 --> 01:07:17,449
She's an innocent girl
who doesn't know anything

1529
01:07:17,450 --> 01:07:20,827
about your filthy world
filled with guns and blood.

1530
01:07:20,828 --> 01:07:24,289
If you really care about
her, stay away from her.

1531
01:07:24,290 --> 01:07:28,961
I'm warning you, the next time
I see you, I will shoot you.

1532
01:07:32,673 --> 01:07:35,717
Have I been wrong all these years?

1533
01:07:35,718 --> 01:07:38,220
(piano music)

1534
01:08:01,827 --> 01:08:03,953
(machine gun firing)

1535
01:08:03,954 --> 01:08:07,041
(soldiers shrieking)

1536
01:08:08,334 --> 01:08:10,418
- Hey, leave some for me to shoot.

1537
01:08:10,419 --> 01:08:12,630
- Would you hurry up and go rescue Kaori?

1538
01:08:15,341 --> 01:08:17,967
(Falcon panting)

1539
01:08:17,968 --> 01:08:20,345
(machine guns firing)

1540
01:08:20,346 --> 01:08:22,013
(Falcon grunting)

1541
01:08:22,014 --> 01:08:25,101
(machine gun firing)

1542
01:08:26,602 --> 01:08:31,607
(soldiers shrieking)
(machine gun firing)

1543
01:08:33,567 --> 01:08:36,654
(soldiers screaming)

1544
01:08:37,780 --> 01:08:39,572
(grenades clattering)

1545
01:08:39,573 --> 01:08:40,615
(glass shattering)

1546
01:08:40,616 --> 01:08:45,621
(soldiers yelling)
(explosions booming)

1547
01:08:46,914 --> 01:08:48,873
- I'm growing tired of them.

1548
01:08:48,874 --> 01:08:51,543
(explosions booming)

1549
01:08:51,544 --> 01:08:54,879
(soldiers shrieking)
(building rumbling)

1550
01:08:54,880 --> 01:08:58,675
(soldiers yelling)
(building rumbling)

1551
01:08:58,676 --> 01:09:01,386
(Laipnitz yelling)

1552
01:09:01,387 --> 01:09:04,390
(building rumbling)

1553
01:09:07,643 --> 01:09:10,270
(Gunther panting)

1554
01:09:10,271 --> 01:09:11,896
- I don't believe it.

1555
01:09:11,897 --> 01:09:13,857
The special forces are losing.

1556
01:09:13,858 --> 01:09:17,193
(piano music)

1557
01:09:17,194 --> 01:09:18,862
- [Oigen] Sir.

1558
01:09:18,863 --> 01:09:19,863
- Hm?

1559
01:09:21,740 --> 01:09:22,740
I see.

1560
01:09:30,082 --> 01:09:31,500
- Colonel Helzen.

1561
01:09:36,005 --> 01:09:38,591
(gun clacking)

1562
01:09:39,633 --> 01:09:44,012
(rubble rumbling)
(Laipnitz grunting)

1563
01:09:44,013 --> 01:09:45,054
- Huh?

1564
01:09:45,055 --> 01:09:46,723
(Lapinitz yelling)

1565
01:09:46,724 --> 01:09:48,224
(gun clattering)

1566
01:09:48,225 --> 01:09:50,895
(both grunting)

1567
01:09:54,565 --> 01:09:59,570
(pipe whooshing)
(both grunting)

1568
01:10:00,446 --> 01:10:01,613
(Falcon laughing)

1569
01:10:01,614 --> 01:10:02,573
- Huh?

1570
01:10:02,574 --> 01:10:05,617
(Falcon yelling)

1571
01:10:05,618 --> 01:10:07,493
- Son of swine.

1572
01:10:07,494 --> 01:10:08,870
Hm.

1573
01:10:08,871 --> 01:10:10,205
(Laipnitz grunting)

1574
01:10:10,206 --> 01:10:11,331
