1575
01:10:11,332 --> 01:10:12,832
(Laipnitz grunting)

1576
01:10:12,833 --> 01:10:14,709
(Laipnitz yelling)

1577
01:10:14,710 --> 01:10:17,546
(rubble rumbling)

1578
01:10:26,555 --> 01:10:27,931
(Bondal shrieking)

1579
01:10:27,932 --> 01:10:30,684
(Bondal panting)

1580
01:10:34,647 --> 01:10:35,813
- Somebody's coming.

1581
01:10:35,814 --> 01:10:37,899
(metal clicking)
(Kaori gasping)

1582
01:10:37,900 --> 01:10:40,360
- Everything's ruined now
because of your friends.

1583
01:10:40,361 --> 01:10:41,361
You're coming with me.

1584
01:10:41,362 --> 01:10:42,528
- Like hell we are.

1585
01:10:42,529 --> 01:10:45,615
There's no way you're gonna
use us for protection.

1586
01:10:45,616 --> 01:10:48,201
- Fine, then you will both die here.

1587
01:10:48,202 --> 01:10:50,411
(Kaori gasping)

1588
01:10:50,412 --> 01:10:52,121
(footsteps clicking)

1589
01:10:52,122 --> 01:10:53,122
Huh?

1590
01:10:54,041 --> 01:10:55,041
Get back.

1591
01:10:59,004 --> 01:11:01,173
- You don't learn very well, do you?

1592
01:11:02,633 --> 01:11:04,425
- Joe, I knew you would come.

1593
01:11:04,426 --> 01:11:05,802
- Stay back.

1594
01:11:05,803 --> 01:11:08,304
- I swear, if you hurt that woman at all,

1595
01:11:08,305 --> 01:11:10,306
I'm not gonna let you live.

1596
01:11:10,307 --> 01:11:11,641
- I'll take my chances.

1597
01:11:11,642 --> 01:11:13,394
Now throw the gun away.

1598
01:11:14,311 --> 01:11:15,520
(Gunther shrieking)

1599
01:11:15,521 --> 01:11:17,146
(Klaus grunting)

1600
01:11:17,147 --> 01:11:18,147
- Klaus.

1601
01:11:19,566 --> 01:11:20,608
(gun firing)

1602
01:11:20,609 --> 01:11:23,612
(Gunther shrieking)

1603
01:11:26,782 --> 01:11:27,907
- Sorry about that.

1604
01:11:27,908 --> 01:11:31,620
Maybe you could get a disability
transfer to a desk job.

1605
01:11:34,540 --> 01:11:35,374
Thanks, Klaus.

1606
01:11:35,375 --> 01:11:37,208
Couldn't have done it without you.

1607
01:11:37,209 --> 01:11:38,002
- Oh.

1608
01:11:38,003 --> 01:11:39,502
It was nothing.

1609
01:11:39,503 --> 01:11:40,337
- All right.

1610
01:11:40,338 --> 01:11:41,630
Let's get outta here.
- Right.

1611
01:11:42,506 --> 01:11:45,550
(all panting)

1612
01:11:45,551 --> 01:11:49,137
(Gunther laughing)

1613
01:11:49,138 --> 01:11:51,806
- Nothing matters now.

1614
01:11:51,807 --> 01:11:54,727
(Gunther laughing)

1615
01:12:07,072 --> 01:12:09,742
(door creaking)

1616
01:12:11,201 --> 01:12:14,121
(Gunther laughing)

1617
01:12:14,955 --> 01:12:17,999
Damn every last one of you to hell!

1618
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:21,003
(explosion roaring)

1619
01:12:32,556 --> 01:12:35,225
(all screaming)

1620
01:12:38,979 --> 01:12:42,148
(Bondal whimpering)

1621
01:12:42,149 --> 01:12:45,152
(building rumbling)

1622
01:13:02,878 --> 01:13:03,878
- Ah, no.

1623
01:13:05,547 --> 01:13:06,547
Le Proges.

1624
01:13:16,433 --> 01:13:19,018
Oh, Helzen, thank God you're okay.

1625
01:13:19,019 --> 01:13:19,853
Kill them.

1626
01:13:19,854 --> 01:13:21,521
They're all against us.

1627
01:13:21,522 --> 01:13:24,274
(flames roaring)

1628
01:13:25,150 --> 01:13:26,567
- [Joe] What do you want?

1629
01:13:26,568 --> 01:13:28,361
- I want to find closure.

1630
01:13:28,362 --> 01:13:29,196
- [Joe] Hm.

1631
01:13:29,197 --> 01:13:31,906
- I loved Sophia deeply,
with all my heart.

1632
01:13:31,907 --> 01:13:34,450
I loved her so much that I
wanted everything in life

1633
01:13:34,451 --> 01:13:35,868
to be perfect for her.

1634
01:13:35,869 --> 01:13:38,913
I could have brought Sophia
with me to East Galiera.

1635
01:13:38,914 --> 01:13:40,998
In fact, she wanted me to do so,

1636
01:13:40,999 --> 01:13:42,083
but I didn't want to drag her

1637
01:13:42,084 --> 01:13:44,544
into this horrible
existence that we share.

1638
01:13:44,545 --> 01:13:47,130
You know what I'm
talking about, Mr. Saeba.

1639
01:13:47,131 --> 01:13:49,298
I thought it was best that
I stay as far as possible

1640
01:13:49,299 --> 01:13:51,843
from her and the baby she expected.

1641
01:13:51,844 --> 01:13:54,805
I knew that my very presence
would endanger their wellbeing.

1642
01:13:55,681 --> 01:13:58,975
So I disappeared, never to be seen again.

1643
01:13:58,976 --> 01:14:02,520
But now that I know of Nina
and all her pain and confusion,

1644
01:14:02,521 --> 01:14:05,189
I don't know whether that
was the right thing to do.

1645
01:14:05,190 --> 01:14:06,859
Maybe I was just a coward.

1646
01:14:08,068 --> 01:14:10,528
- Please, Helzen, that's enough.

1647
01:14:10,529 --> 01:14:11,529
Stop.

1648
01:14:12,656 --> 01:14:14,699
Everything is all my fault.

1649
01:14:14,700 --> 01:14:16,909
I pushed you away from her.

1650
01:14:16,910 --> 01:14:17,828
- You're wrong.

1651
01:14:17,829 --> 01:14:19,328
It wasn't your fault, Klaus.

1652
01:14:19,329 --> 01:14:22,373
Even if you hadn't told me to
disappear from Sophia's life,

1653
01:14:22,374 --> 01:14:25,126
I had already gathered
my courage to withdraw.

1654
01:14:25,127 --> 01:14:25,961
- Helzen.

1655
01:14:25,961 --> 01:14:26,879
- What's he talking about?

1656
01:14:26,880 --> 01:14:28,087
It doesn't make sense.

1657
01:14:28,088 --> 01:14:29,297
Is he sick?

1658
01:14:29,298 --> 01:14:30,591
Joe, what's happening?

1659
01:14:31,800 --> 01:14:32,801
- A duel.

1660
01:14:34,178 --> 01:14:35,303
- Joe.

1661
01:14:35,304 --> 01:14:38,055
- Falcon will assist us
as the official witness.

1662
01:14:38,056 --> 01:14:39,265
All right?

1663
01:14:39,266 --> 01:14:40,267
- [Helzen] That's fine.

1664
01:14:41,310 --> 01:14:44,062
(flames roaring)

1665
01:14:46,690 --> 01:14:49,317
(gun clicking)

1666
01:14:49,318 --> 01:14:51,194
(bullets clattering)

1667
01:14:51,195 --> 01:14:53,947
(bullet chiming)

1668
01:14:55,199 --> 01:14:56,616
- Please stop.

1669
01:14:56,617 --> 01:14:58,534
I don't understand why you
have to shoot each other

1670
01:14:58,535 --> 01:14:59,660
like this.

1671
01:14:59,661 --> 01:15:02,372
(flames roaring)

1672
01:15:10,422 --> 01:15:12,883
(piano music)

1673
01:15:47,334 --> 01:15:49,418
(gun firing)

1674
01:15:49,419 --> 01:15:50,254
(gun firing)

1675
01:15:50,255 --> 01:15:53,090
(Falcon grunting)

1676
01:15:54,299 --> 01:15:57,677
(Joe grunting)

1677
01:15:57,678 --> 01:15:58,678
- Joe!

1678
01:15:59,471 --> 01:16:01,974
(piano music)

1679
01:16:05,852 --> 01:16:09,022
(audience applauding)

1680
01:16:15,028 --> 01:16:16,028
Joe, Joe.

1681
01:16:17,114 --> 01:16:18,198
Come on, Joe.

1682
01:16:20,993 --> 01:16:21,827
- I'm fine.

1683
01:16:21,828 --> 01:16:23,035
Just a bit winded.

1684
01:16:23,036 --> 01:16:26,289
(chimes ringing)

1685
01:16:26,290 --> 01:16:29,042
(flames roaring)

1686
01:16:29,960 --> 01:16:31,586
- The pendant.

1687
01:16:31,587 --> 01:16:32,920
It's been broken.

1688
01:16:32,921 --> 01:16:35,256
(piano wire snapping)
(audience applauding)

1689
01:16:35,257 --> 01:16:37,843
(Nina gasping)

1690
01:16:45,309 --> 01:16:50,314
(Helzen groaning)
(dramatic music)

1691
01:16:51,690 --> 01:16:54,191
- I think that the pain in my heart

1692
01:16:54,192 --> 01:16:56,736
equals the pain I have caused Nina.

1693
01:16:56,737 --> 01:17:00,114
Tell her that I loved her.

1694
01:17:00,115 --> 01:17:03,451
(Helzen groaning)

1695
01:17:03,452 --> 01:17:05,286
(Bondal shrieking)

1696
01:17:05,287 --> 01:17:06,705
- [Bondal] Somebody help me!

1697
01:17:11,418 --> 01:17:13,502
- Oh dear God in heaven, Helzen.

1698
01:17:13,503 --> 01:17:14,463
No.

1699
01:17:14,464 --> 01:17:16,339
Don't leave us now.

1700
01:17:16,340 --> 01:17:19,092
(dramatic music)

1701
01:17:28,226 --> 01:17:29,478
- [Oigen] Colonel Helzen.

1702
01:17:37,736 --> 01:17:40,154
(tires squealing)

1703
01:17:40,155 --> 01:17:41,447
(Bondal panting)

1704
01:17:41,448 --> 01:17:42,366
- [Bondal] Wake up.

1705
01:17:42,367 --> 01:17:44,033
Is anybody there?

1706
01:17:44,034 --> 01:17:45,534
It's me.

1707
01:17:45,535 --> 01:17:48,288
(Bondal panting)

1708
01:17:52,334 --> 01:17:56,087
- [Man] It seems you've made
a bit of a mess, Bondal.

1709
01:17:56,088 --> 01:17:56,922
- Who are you supposed to be?

1710
01:17:56,923 --> 01:17:59,715
Oigen, who the hell is this man?

1711
01:17:59,716 --> 01:18:03,052
Why are you in my office
without my approval?

1712
01:18:03,053 --> 01:18:06,013
- I'd like you to meet
Chief Investigator Steiner

1713
01:18:06,014 --> 01:18:09,350
of our Special Intelligence Division.

1714
01:18:09,351 --> 01:18:11,144
- The Special Intelligence Division?

1715
01:18:12,354 --> 01:18:13,604
- You will have an opportunity

1716
01:18:13,605 --> 01:18:16,065
to explain yourself when we return.

1717
01:18:16,066 --> 01:18:18,776
But I don't think you'll
escape serving time

1718
01:18:18,777 --> 01:18:21,863
in the concentration camps for
all the harm you have caused.

1719
01:18:22,948 --> 01:18:25,158
- I can't go to the camps.

1720
01:18:26,618 --> 01:18:30,371
(Bondal whimpering)

1721
01:18:30,372 --> 01:18:32,915
- Helzen has died on the job.

1722
01:18:32,916 --> 01:18:34,542
God.

1723
01:18:34,543 --> 01:18:37,002
He and I joined the service together.

1724
01:18:37,003 --> 01:18:38,964
This is such a waste.

1725
01:18:40,674 --> 01:18:44,218
I suppose that he is living
in heaven now with Sophia.

1726
01:18:44,219 --> 01:18:46,679
In a way, I envy him.

1727
01:18:46,680 --> 01:18:49,433
(dramatic music)

1728
01:18:58,400 --> 01:19:01,360
- [Passenger] Ah, you
know, we're going down-

1729
01:19:01,361 --> 01:19:05,406
- I hope I don't-
(passengers chattering)

1730
01:19:05,407 --> 01:19:07,241
- Thank you for everything.

1731
01:19:07,242 --> 01:19:08,325
- You're welcome.

1732
01:19:08,326 --> 01:19:09,161
Here.

1733
01:19:09,162 --> 01:19:10,370
Let me return this to you.

1734
01:19:11,371 --> 01:19:13,706
I know how important
this keepsake was to you.

1735
01:19:13,707 --> 01:19:15,958
I'm very sorry it got damaged.

1736
01:19:15,959 --> 01:19:17,042
- Don't be.

1737
01:19:17,043 --> 01:19:20,963
I'm glad this pendant was
able to save you, Mr. Saeba.

1738
01:19:20,964 --> 01:19:22,549
You're the one I...

1739
01:19:23,842 --> 01:19:27,344
(boat whistle blowing)

1740
01:19:27,345 --> 01:19:30,682
(passengers chattering)

1741
01:19:37,814 --> 01:19:41,067
(boat whistle blowing)

1742
01:19:45,781 --> 01:19:46,615
- [Nina Voiceover] It wouldn't be right

1743
01:19:46,616 --> 01:19:49,116
to come between the two of them.

1744
01:19:49,117 --> 01:19:51,536
It's better that I leave
without saying anything.

1745
01:19:54,080 --> 01:19:55,164
(engine revving)

1746
01:19:55,165 --> 01:19:56,999
- Bye.
- Bye.

1747
01:19:57,000 --> 01:19:59,085
- [Woman] Gonna miss you.

1748
01:20:01,087 --> 01:20:03,672
- I've just been handed the final report.

1749
01:20:03,673 --> 01:20:05,633
East Galiera has confirmed the death

1750
01:20:05,634 --> 01:20:08,636
of Mr. Helzen in the line of duty.

1751
01:20:08,637 --> 01:20:09,637
- Excellent.

1752
01:20:12,474 --> 01:20:15,977
- [Nina Voiceover] Kaori and
Joe, they have each other.

1753
01:20:17,437 --> 01:20:19,064
But I don't have anyone now.

1754
01:20:35,413 --> 01:20:37,998
(piano music)

1755
01:20:37,999 --> 01:20:41,210
(Nina gasping)

1756
01:20:41,211 --> 01:20:44,213
- I can see by your face that
you're surprised to see me.

1757
01:20:44,214 --> 01:20:47,132
It just so happens that
the gunshot to my chest

1758
01:20:47,133 --> 01:20:49,343
was not sufficient to kill me.

1759
01:20:49,344 --> 01:20:50,886
- Thank God.

1760
01:20:50,887 --> 01:20:52,764
But Mr. Saeba didn't say anything.

1761
01:20:53,682 --> 01:20:55,683
- We didn't intend to deceive you,

1762
01:20:55,684 --> 01:20:57,059
but we couldn't tell you anything

1763
01:20:57,060 --> 01:20:59,937
until the government in East
Galiera confirmed my death,

1764
01:20:59,938 --> 01:21:02,523
or all this pain would have
been for nothing, my daughter.

1765
01:21:02,524 --> 01:21:06,402
Helzen the intelligence
officer is now truly dead.

1766
01:21:06,403 --> 01:21:08,320
And so, there is no reason anymore

1767
01:21:08,321 --> 01:21:10,698
for me to go back to East Galiera.

1768
01:21:10,699 --> 01:21:12,116
- Father.

1769
01:21:12,117 --> 01:21:13,450
I'm so...

1770
01:21:13,451 --> 01:21:15,244
I'm so confused.

1771
01:21:15,245 --> 01:21:17,079
This is so sudden.

1772
01:21:17,080 --> 01:21:19,624
- All you need to know is
that I'm not leaving you.

1773
01:21:20,542 --> 01:21:23,628
I'd like to make up for the
last 20 years that I've missed.

1774
01:21:24,588 --> 01:21:25,880
- Oh.

1775
01:21:25,881 --> 01:21:30,886
(Nina sobbing)
(piano music)

1776
01:21:31,678 --> 01:21:33,305
I can't believe it.

1777
01:21:34,306 --> 01:21:35,307
It's not a dream.

1778
01:21:37,309 --> 01:21:39,895
(Nina sobbing)

1779
01:21:47,277 --> 01:21:48,944
(engine revving)

1780
01:21:48,945 --> 01:21:49,945
- So?
- Hm?

1781
01:21:50,655 --> 01:21:53,032
- Does this mean that
Joe's nearly perfect record

1782
01:21:53,033 --> 01:21:54,491
survived the fight?

1783
01:21:54,492 --> 01:21:55,327
- Maybe.

1784
01:21:55,328 --> 01:21:58,162
This duel was about something much deeper

1785
01:21:58,163 --> 01:22:00,539
than just defeating the opponent.

1786
01:22:00,540 --> 01:22:03,208
It was a test of a
different kind of honor.

1787
01:22:03,209 --> 01:22:07,714
And if anyone's going to
kill Joe, it'll be me.

1788
01:22:08,673 --> 01:22:11,926
(both laughing)
(saxophone music)

1789
01:22:11,927 --> 01:22:13,385
- Nice work, Joe.

1790
01:22:13,386 --> 01:22:15,512
I wouldn't have come up
with an idea like that,

1791
01:22:15,513 --> 01:22:18,390
decreasing the amount of
powder in one of your rounds?

1792
01:22:18,391 --> 01:22:21,143
Amazing that you had just
the right amount to penetrate

1793
01:22:21,144 --> 01:22:23,479
but not go all the way to his heart.

1794
01:22:23,480 --> 01:22:25,773
- Sure it was a risky way to do it,

1795
01:22:25,774 --> 01:22:27,107
but the plan might've failed

1796
01:22:27,108 --> 01:22:29,736
if the wound didn't appear
completely authentic.

1797
01:22:30,779 --> 01:22:31,779
Wait.

1798
01:22:31,780 --> 01:22:33,238
I brought you something.

1799
01:22:33,239 --> 01:22:34,239
Here.

1800
01:22:35,200 --> 01:22:36,784
- You can keep it.

1801
01:22:36,785 --> 01:22:39,371
With Bondal gone, I don't need it anymore.

1802
01:22:41,790 --> 01:22:43,624
- Joe, I'm sorry.

1803
01:22:43,625 --> 01:22:46,251
That was such a foolish
mistake that I made.

1804
01:22:46,252 --> 01:22:48,004
I shouldn't be your partner anymore.

1805
01:22:50,048 --> 01:22:52,591
- If you hadn't taken that
incredible helicopter ride,

1806
01:22:52,592 --> 01:22:55,552
I might've never found out
where they were keeping Klaus.

1807
01:22:55,553 --> 01:22:56,972
I need you as a partner.

1808
01:22:59,140 --> 01:23:00,307
- Joe.

1809
01:23:00,308 --> 01:23:03,853
(pleasant saxophone music)

1810
01:23:08,817 --> 01:23:10,067
- [Helzen Voiceover] Mr. Saeba,

1811
01:23:10,068 --> 01:23:12,070
I have what I was looking for.

1812
01:23:14,280 --> 01:23:15,781
But to see what you need,

1813
01:23:15,782 --> 01:23:18,200
you need to look a little
closer from now on.

1814
01:23:18,201 --> 01:23:22,413
(gull cawing)
(metal clanking)

1815
01:23:22,414 --> 01:23:25,250
(water splashing)

1816
01:23:28,378 --> 01:23:31,548
(upbeat heroic music)

1817
01:23:50,025 --> 01:23:53,820
(singing in foreign language)

